# youchop.app — server env (set these in the Vercel project, not committed)
# The "Channel → Text" tool (/extract) uses two FREE backends:

# 1) Channel search + video listing — YouTube Data API v3 (FREE, 10,000 units/day).
#    Create a key: Google Cloud Console → enable "YouTube Data API v3" → Credentials → API key.
#    No billing required for the free quota. search costs 100 units, listing ~1 unit / 50 videos.
YT_DATA_API_KEY=

# 2) Transcripts — Apify (FREE tier: $5/mo credits). Apify runs the scrape on their
#    infra, so it survives YouTube's datacenter-IP blocking that kills direct scraping
#    on Vercel. Get the token: apify.com → Settings → API & Integrations → Personal API token.
#    Default actor: karamelo/youtube-transcripts (~$0.007/video). Override with APIFY_TRANSCRIPT_ACTOR.
APIFY_TOKEN=
# APIFY_TRANSCRIPT_ACTOR=karamelo~youtube-transcripts

# Optional overrides:
# TRANSCRIPT_PROVIDER=apify        # force a provider: "apify" or "ytio" (default: auto from whichever key exists)

# Optional PAID fallback — youtube-transcript.io (Plus $9.99/mo). Only used if TRANSCRIPT_PROVIDER=ytio
# or if APIFY_TOKEN is absent. Paste ONLY the token (code prepends "Basic ").
YT_TRANSCRIPT_TOKEN=
